    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-10-18T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-10-18T04:00:00-05:00" n="433"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d433">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1163 Seventh Day Adventist/48: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-10-18T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >October 18, 1937—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:24 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>865. Last night during the course of an air raid on Hongkew and Yangtzepoo areas,
                    Chinese planes dropped one or more incendiary bombs on the property of the
                    Seventh Day Adventist Mission, located at 526 Ningkuo Road, Yangtzepoo. One
                    large two storied brick building was struck by incendiary bomb and completely
                    destroyed by fire. It is requested that Embassy bring this to the attention of
                    the Chinese Government with a protest on the bombing and destruction of American
                    property by Chinese planes.</p>
                <p>2. During their several raids last night Chinese planes again flew over the
                    foreign protected area at Shanghai thus drawing Japanese anti-aircraft fire and
                    endangering foreign and Chinese noncombatants <pb facs="0376" n="368"
                        xml:id="pg_368"/> to a repetition of the frightful slaughter of bloody
                    Saturday, August 14.</p>
                <p>Sent to Nanking. Repeated to the Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
